<br>
They do have that option if they really want to, xaanru.  That very thing has been suggested by people who don't like the list.  I've seen more than one person say that what they would do is camp it too and then try to assemble the force first.  At least in that case both people would have put in equal time camping it.  What you were saying was that as long as someone doesn't put their name on the list, it's perfectly fine for them to come in at the last minute and grab ragefire away from someone who's spent weeks camping it.  As long as no Verant rules are broken, it's perfectly fine.  And yes, I consider such an opinion to be pathetic, or maybe more sad than anything.  It's not you personally, just that particular opinion of yours.  Now throw out arguments about The List from what I was saying.  I wasn't commenting on the fairness or unfairness of that list at all.  Generalizing to apply to all behavior that doesn't break the rules/laws was simply following the logical progression of the view posted by yourself and others who also used the &quot;No Verant rules were broken!&quot; mantra like that justified anything.. <br>
<br>
Again, I wasn't commenting on the fairness of the list at all so maybe that was a misunderstanding.  I was commenting on one person having a mob camped for an incredibly long time only to have someone else come in at the last minute and take it.  To knowingly do so would be a total lack of respect for the original person's effort and in my opinion an all around lousy thing to do.   As for your claim that keeping a character logged in and camping the same spot for over a week requires little effort and apparently from that argument, isn't enough effort to bother respecting.  For most people devoting that much time to it is an insane amount of effort, so much so that they will never do their cleric epic.  It's far far from trivial, at least for most of us who play the game.<br>
<br>
-- Callon<br>
