<br>
What I -hear- (rumor alert) is that the entire raid took place, rage was killed the required two times(human, dragon), and the clerics on the hill were not even sure IF it had happened or not. Sounds to me like they were not paying attention.<br>
<br>
I'm a strong supporter of the list.   I have clerics in my guild way down the list.  I've helped clerics I've never heard of before or since get their epics with it. But folks on the hill need to do their job-- it is earned, not a gimme. It is a WONDERFUL alternative to 8 clerics sitting there followed by a massive KS fest. <br>
<br>
But Epics are uberland and uberland includes getting a credible force there in a reasonable amount of time. If folks are afk for 20-30 minutes at a time, they can't expect folks to sit back and do nothing.<br>
<br>
If you think it is stupid to sit there for 12 days to do the camp, think back to when the list started-- sitting there for 12 days followed by a massive KS fest-- one person walks away the winner- the rest settle down to another 12 days and only one of them -- or even some random person-- will win.<br>
  Guilds rushing multiple times to SF and leaving with nothing but bitter confrontation and defeat.And it was always almost always one of the &quot;uber&quot; guilds that won the confrontation which gave them even more power to recruit clerics away from lower guilds since they could deliver epics and then more power to recruit folks since they had cleric epics for their raids.   There were clerics there for 30-40 days when they finally decided to set up the list.   The list is a godsend for &quot;casual&quot; and even fairly serious players as it allows them to pool their strength and to focus their vacation time to one camp.  It is the group might of the hobbesians vs the individual might of the nietzchians.<br>
<br>
  It is not perfect or fair or any more moral than the other systems but it is a lot more efficient for the clerics involved.  As it is even the &quot;easy&quot; 12-14 day camp can strain marriages and people's health.<br>
<br>
It's very unfortunate about the LD. From what I've seen here Melissa is prepared to be nice about it, but it is not cut and dried to me that she should.  Have to agree with Ullas that if she did it would not be bad for her rep.<br>
