What you were saying was that as long as someone doesn't put their name on the list, it's perfectly fine for them to come in at the last minute and grab ragefire away from someone who's spent weeks camping it. As long as no Verant rules are broken, it's perfectly fine.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
try to avoid putting words into my mouth, particularly when you don't understand what I am saying. Doing that would be... what's the word you like so much.. &quot;pathetic&quot;.<br>
<br>
What I said was :<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
A cleric, who is not a supporter of the list, came into skyfire and found rage up. The only people camping the spawn were two afk clerics. This person (melissa?) had time to assemble a raid force, and killed rage, having engaged it first, NOT KSed, which per Verant policy on spawns, makes it their mob.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You read this as:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
Xaanru's post suggesting that if someone wasn't on the list, swooped in at the last minute, and aggro'ed the spawn first, then it's just fine as long as they didn't break any Verant rules really bugs me<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Where did I say anything about swooping, grabbing away from someone who is currently camping, or anything about how long the person had been camping.<br>
<br>
What you fail to realize, is that the list, as it exists, guarantees that someone is &quot;camping&quot; (in theory) rage at all times (even if they are not there for up to two hours, according to the list rules) for the next two years. The bottom line is, it doesn't matter if a cleric were to sit there for one whole month, watching spawns get taken by the List members, then claim a spawn as theirs, becuase they were the only one in the zone when rage popped. Supporters of the list would still claim a camp steal. <br>
<br>
The fact is, and this was horrible luck on the part of the #1 cleric, is that there was nobody camping the spawn, when melissa got there. 2 afk clerics, who do not respond for enough time to assemble a raid force, kill the human form and dragon form rage (and still these people do not respond) is not camping. The one &quot;live&quot; camper, had a linkdead. I agree that is awful timing, and it sucks. However, that notwithstanding, Melissa found the spawn uncamped, up, and nobody assembling troops. The two characters parked in the zone as placeholders do not count as camping in my eyes. There was nobody behind the characters.<br>
<br>
My point is, for non-list supporters, situations like this are the only chance they have to get ragefire. It was not KSing, and only in the loosest possible interpretation could it be considered camp stealing. The point I was making is, as a list supporter, she knew it was camped, knew who was camping it, and had agreed to respect the camp, including the current rules for said camp (including the 2 hour rule involving linkdead clerics) and that is what makes it different (and since she was #8 on the list (/boggle), as part of the top 10 clerics, she could have changed the rules if she didn't like them). <br>
<br>
If some other cleric, having no such agreement, went to skyshrine, hailed and talked to the only two (afk) clerics there, and when he or she, over a significant period of time, got no response, assembled troops and took down zordak, then the dragon Rage, how could they possibly be considered KSers. Look at it this way, if there were no list, and I had gone in to camp ragefire, sat there for 5 days, and then my ISP went down, am I still camping? If you come into the zone, and find that I am not there, and ragefire is up, are you KSing if you kill him (particularly considering that I do not log back in for well over half an hour, long enough for you to get troops up, and kill zordak)? I say no. I also will always maintain that a toon with nobody behind it is not camping a mob, its just sitting there. Now, if you still find that pathetic, I pity you, for your twisted sense of ethics.<br>
<br>
BTW, my comment about the effort was in essence to say that sitting in the zone is less significant that completing the other parts of the quest. Someone who has killed ALL of the other quest mobs, has done something significant. The List does not recognize that effort, by locking a large portion of the server (even those who have completed the rest of the quest) out from the rage camp for at least two years. Compared to the achievement of having gotten the rest of the epic quest done, parking your character in skyshrine for a week really isn't that tough.<br>
<br>
Now, if you disagree, feel free to express your own opinions, but stop trying to put words into my mouth, or twist what I said into something it isn't. <br>
<br>
